Date: Mon, 19 May 2014 19:23:22 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 0422/1369] drm/i915: Drop bogus comments about display reset
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

commit a83d87fda6932980fa3081e56fe081ef3dbd767a upstream.

There are comments in the gen4-5 reset functions stating that we can't
reset render and media without also doing a display reset. But that's
exactly what the code does, ie. we don't perform a display reset. Drop
the bogus comments.

Signed-off-by: Ville Syrjälä <ville.syrjala@linux.intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Jesse Barnes <jbarnes@virtuousgeek.org>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_uncore.c |    2 --
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_uncore.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_uncore.c
index 0f75f3e..bea2de4 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_uncore.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_uncore.c
@@ -980,7 +980,6 @@ static int i965_do_reset(struct drm_device *dev)
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
 
-	/* We can't reset render&media without also resetting display ... */
 	pci_write_config_byte(dev->pdev, I965_GDRST,
 			      GRDOM_MEDIA | GRDOM_RESET_ENABLE);
 
@@ -1007,7 +1006,6 @@ static int ironlake_do_reset(struct drm_device *dev)
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
 
-	/* We can't reset render&media without also resetting display ... */
 	gdrst = I915_READ(MCHBAR_MIRROR_BASE + ILK_GDSR);
 	gdrst &= ~GRDOM_MASK;
 	I915_WRITE(MCHBAR_MIRROR_BASE + ILK_GDSR,
